title: Group action

If $$G$$ is a [[group|Gruppe]] and $$X$$ is any set, then an //action// $$\theta$$ of $$G$$ on $$X$$ is a map

$$
\theta\colon G\times X\to X,\quad (g,x)\mapsto g\cdot x\coloneqq \theta_g(x)
$$

Such that $$\theta_e=\id_X$$ and $$\theta_{gh}=\theta_g \circ \theta_h.$$ The action $$\theta$$ partitions $$X$$ into //orbits//

$$
G\cdot x\coloneqq \{\, g\cdot x\mid g\in G \,\},
$$

which are the equivalence classes under the [[equivalence relation|Ã„quivalenzrelation]] $$x\sim g\cdot x.$$